comments: McDaniels (MIN) maintains verticality and absorbs the contact that occurs during Bridges's (BKN) driving shot attempt.
Edwards (MIN) places his forearm to Finney-Smith's (BKN) front and marginal contact occurs as Edwards releases away during the drive.
Edwards (MIN) does not overtly or abruptly extend his leg out as marginal contact occurs with Finney-Smith (BKN) during the jump shot attempt.
Conley (MIN) immediately slides his hand off of O'Neale's (BKN) side and marginal contact occurs during the pick.
Anderson (MIN) hedges the pick and marginal contact occurs to Dinwiddie's (BKN) front during his drive to the basket.
Anderson (MIN) initiates contact with Dinwiddie's (BKN) body, which affects his driving shot attempt.
O'Neale (BKN) and Towns (MIN) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Johnson (BKN) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he moves to imminently guard an opponent.

Towns (MIN) slightly extends his arm back and incidental contact occurs to O'Neale's (BKN) face as they come together in the post.  Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
O'Neale (BKN) initiates contact with Towns' (MIN) arm, which affects his play at the basket.
Edwards (MIN) brings his arm toward Dinwiddie's (BKN) path and marginal contact occurs during Dinwiddie's drive in transition.
Finney-Smith (BKN) establishes himself in Edwards's (MIN) path and absorbs the contact.
Conley (MIN) makes contact with the ball as Finney-Smith (BKN) gathers the ball and dislodges it away during his driving shot attempt before incidental arm contact occurs.

Replay review of the foul called on Finney-Smith (BKN) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Finney-Smith (BKN) is the last person to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds. The possession is correctly given to MIN.
Towns (MIN) establishes himself in Dinwiddie's (BKN) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
Towns (MIN) briefly engages with O'Neale (BKN) in the lane before correcting.
Towns (MIN) is imminently exiting the lane within three seconds.
O'Neale (BKN) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Bridges (BKN) swipes down and initiates contact with Edwards' (MIN) arm that affects his driving shot attempt.
Edwards (MIN) brings his arm toward Dinwiddie's (BKN) path and marginal contact occurs during Dinwiddie's drive.
Bridges (BKN) and Edwards (MIN) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Johnson (BKN) commits a take foul on Conley (MIN).
null
McDaniels (MIN) briefly places his hands to Bridges' (BKN) body off ball before correcting.
Edwards (MIN) and Dinwiddie (BKN) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Edwards (MIN) makes contact with Dinwiddie's (BKN) arm during his upward shooting motion and the contact affects his jump shot attempt.
Edwards (MIN) is the last person to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds. The possession is correctly given to BKN.
Finney-Smith (BKN) absorbs the contact to his chest from Edwards (MIN) as he moves towards his front during the screen.  Marginal contact takes place as he moves over it.
Anderson (MIN) legally contests Dinwiddie's (BKN) jump shot attempt.
Finney-Smith (BKN) commits a take foul on Edwards (MIN).
